The Minister of Women Affairs Pauline Talen, has recovered from the ravaging Coronavirus.  The Minister who released a statement on Monday, January 4 announcing that she has tested negative for the virus thanked Nigerian women and the entire nation for the prayers and unshakeable dedication to the plight of those declared positive of the Coronavirus disease. Talen also urged members of the public to comply with the COVID-19 guidelines to be safe. Source By Justina Auta Abuja - The United Nations on Wednesday donated N38.4 million for procurement of palliatives targeted at the vulnerable and indigent women across 14 states to cushion the hardship caused by the COVID-19 pandemic. Ms Comfort Lamptey, UN Women Country Representative to Nigeria and ECOWAS, made this known… May 6, 2020 In "Health" By Ismaila Chafe Abuja - The Federal Executive Council (FEC) on Wednesday endorsed stiffer penalties against rapists and child abusers as proposed by the Ministry of Women Affairs, describing the upsurge as embarrassing. The Minister of Women Affairs, Mrs Pauline Tallen, made this known at the end of the fourth… June 10, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Justina Auta Abuja - The Minister of Women Affairs, Mrs Pauline Tallen, on Monday urged lawmakers to enact laws and evolve polices that would ensure a safe society and end violence against women and girls. Tallen made the call in the ministry’s official twitter handle, @FMWA-ng in Abuja. She… June 1, 2020 In "Health"